<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="361" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d361">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">811.24 Raw Materials/954:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-20">May 20,
                                    1940</date>.<lb/>[Received May 20—4:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1278. The purport of the Department’s 876, May 16 and 886, May 17,
                                regarding tin has been informally conveyed to the Colonial Office
                                which is looking into the question. In the meantime it would like to
                                know what is the amount of the addition to American stocks which is
                                desired and during what period of time, i. e. both stocks of
                                American tin consumers and the reserve stock in which the Government
                                would be involved. In this connection see the Embassy’s 1247 of May
                                17.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Kennedy</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>